# Tauri IPC bridge

Application code must stay isolated from Tauri implementation details. **Rust `#[tauri::command]` IPC** and **“are we in the desktop webview?”** checks use a dedicated TypeScript boundary, not `@tauri-apps/*` or `window.__TAURI__` scattered through features.

## Canonical bridge

- **`frontend/src/platform/desktop/tauri_ipc_bridge.ts`**
  - Export **`tauriInvoke(cmd, args)`** — all generic command IPC from features/hooks/app shell/core (unless using an approved adapter below).
  - Export **`isTauri()`** — runtime probe; **do not** read `__TAURI_INTERNALS__` / `__TAURI__` in feature modules for this purpose.

## Approved higher-level adapters (invoke already encapsulated)

Use these when they match the domain instead of raw `tauriInvoke`:

- **`frontend/src/platform/desktop/tauri/tauri_gateways.ts`** — `buildTauriFsGateway`, `buildTauriDbGateway`, `buildTauriFormatImportGateway`, `openDevTools`, `isTauriRuntime` (same probe semantics as `isTauri`).
- **`frontend/src/resources/picker_fs_helpers.ts`** — `tauriInvoke` / `isTauriRuntime` for the resource source-picker pipeline.
- **`frontend/src/resources/runtime_config_service.ts`** — cached invoke for app config paths.

New commands needed from UI: call **`tauriInvoke`** from the bridge (or extend an existing gateway in `platform/desktop/` if the operation is FS/DB-shaped).

## Forbidden (application layers)

In **`frontend/src/features/**`, `components/**`, `app_shell/**`, `core/**`, `resources/**`, `hooks/**`** (except files listed under “Infrastructure exceptions”):

- **`import … from "@tauri-apps/api/core"`** for **`invoke`** (and avoid static imports that pull command IPC into features).
- **`window.__TAURI__`**, **`globalThis.__TAURI_INTERNALS__`**, or legacy globals **for IPC** — use **`tauriInvoke`** / **`isTauri`** (or a gateway above).

- **`parts/`** stays **host-agnostic** — no `@tauri-apps/*`. Desktop-only adapters (e.g. UCI **`EngineProcess`** via **`tauri_engine_adapter.ts`**) belong under **`frontend/src/platform/desktop/`**.

## Infrastructure exceptions (only files in this set may import Tauri plugins / specialized APIs directly)

Keep this list **small**; extend only when adding a new integration point and documenting it here:

| Area | Module | Tauri surface |
|------|--------|----------------|
| Logging | `frontend/src/logger.ts` | `@tauri-apps/plugin-log` |
| Native menu | `frontend/src/hooks/useTauriMenu.ts` | `@tauri-apps/api/menu` |
| OTA / relaunch | `frontend/src/app/hooks/useUpdateCheck.ts` | `@tauri-apps/plugin-updater`, `@tauri-apps/plugin-process` |
| Open URL IPC | `frontend/src/resources/open_url.ts` | dynamic `invoke` for `open_external_url` |
| Desktop platform | `frontend/src/platform/desktop/**` | `@tauri-apps/api/*`, gateways, **`tauri_ipc_bridge.ts`**, **`tauri_engine_adapter.ts`** |
| Types only | `frontend/src/resources/tauri_invoke_types.ts` | type-only imports from `@tauri-apps/api/core` |

New **`invoke`** call sites outside `platform/desktop/` and outside this table should **not** be added — route through **`tauri_ipc_bridge`** or move logic into **`platform/desktop/`**.

## Agent checklist

- Before finishing a change that adds IPC: confirm no new `@tauri-apps/api/core` **`invoke`** usage under `features/` / `resources/` except via bridge or listed adapters.
- Prefer **`tauri_ipc_bridge`** for new Rust commands from UI code.
- **Tauri 2 ACL:** Every new **`#[tauri::command]`** registered in **`frontend/src-tauri/src/main.rs`** must be appended to **`frontend/src-tauri/permissions/app-commands.toml`** (`allow-x2chess-app-commands`). Partial allowlists cause **`invoke` permission denied** for unrelated UI (e.g. engine browse, file dialogs).

